[thinking] **Reviewing compatibility and issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering if the project relies solely on our contributions. Might be that rg only included ours because others aren't compatible? I see that Java 17 or 21 could be involved. There's a note about potential issues with using com.sun.net.httpserver regarding Gradle test runtime JVM arguments. As for serialization, ObjectMapper might be acceptable—but still questionable. I'm also thinking about avoiding duplication in tested features when it comes to JSON handling with Person, and ensuring we utilize only public APIs to stay compliant. I see room for improving idiomatic response handling too!
