[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing build issues**\n\nI need to respond regarding a failure that seems related to the environment. The user wants a fix for a failed test command. It seems modifying the build isn't the answer since the disk is full. Our changes to the build.gradle may not have helped. I should check if temp directory creation is failing due to the order of parsed options. Maybe the environment variables aren’t passed correctly or too late. I'll try to untangle this issue.\n\n**Exploring NativeImage issues**\n\nI’m considering the issue with NativeImage.main and its handling of -J-D arguments since the driverRoot is created before processing them. I suspect the TMPDIR environment variable should impact java.io.tmpdir, but maybe addEnvVar isn’t applying. It might ignore TMPDIR because it’s set at native-image build time. I wonder if using the command line option -Djava.io.tmpdir could help if passed correctly. The error for temp directory creation points to a full disk, so I need to find a solution for that.\n\n**Investigating NativeImage construction**\n\nI'm looking into how the Command line arguments work with NativeImage.main. It seems like the constructor might be processed in NativeImage.build when it parses those args. The stack flow indicates that it goes from main to performBuild, then to build, and finally creates a new NativeImage. I’m considering whether it could parse system properties before ArchiveSupport.createTempDir in the constructor. I really need to clarify how all of this interacts during the build process.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02de86cb43a73b800169fe33ec08bc8195a259de4c2ff6b2fd\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_jP2mLrIKBI1ABffl6m27cnQNu1lF44KzM0aPkHotkr_vKnzVArr7X1-7v4hheOeDVLRO8K-Y2fsLdrlNNwcA2LiB8i8ircwlK7ORbCaO5kxCoQ6DPa08QXNGaOrnoOgQc7JV5VX816XvHRiOoZY-MeKu2Qv3_fu63m4U9zvZm3klMM-qPQoUp4bXO79XVYaotc_K4Kq